article.headline: Jamerson carries Norfolk St. past Alabama 80-79 in OT in NIT

images.name: Jones rises up for the alley-oop jam
images.caption: H.erbert Jones catches the lob from John Petty for the thunderous slam.

article.linkText: Jamerson carries Norfolk St. past Alabama 80-79 in OT in NIT
article.story: TUSCALOOSA, Ala. -- Derrik Jamerson Jr. had 25 points and made two free throws with 17 seconds left in overtime as Norfolk State narrowly defeated Alabama 80-79 in the NIT first round on Wednesday night. Nic Thomas had 15 points and five steals for Norfolk State (22-13). Steven Whitley added 13 points, seven rebounds and seven assists. Jordan Butler had 11 points and 12 rebounds for the visitors. Herbert Jones had 18 points for the Crimson Tide (18-16). Alex Reese added 17 points and seven rebounds. John Petty had 11 points, including a 3-pointer to tie it at 67 at the end of regulation. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com

videos.headline: Jamerson hits a tough contested 3
videos.description: Derrik Jamerson Jr. nails the tough 3 to give Norfolk State the lead over Alabama.

videos.headline: Butler misses the wide-open game-winning putback
videos.description: Jordan Butler's missed game-winning putback results in overtime for Norfolk State and Alabama.

videos.headline: Hall cleans up missed alley-oop with a huge putback slam
videos.description: Donta Hall follows up missed fastbreak opportunity with a big time putback dunk for Alabama.

videos.headline: Alabama misses the game-winning shot in OT
videos.description: Alabama gets a chance to win the game after a costly Norfolk State turnover but Riley Norris misses the game-winning shot for Alabama.
